                              ============
                              asciiplanets
                              ============


asciiplanets is an ASCII solar system observer. You can, among other
options, choose the radius to display. This is the inner solar system:

Radius: 1.75 AU                                               2015-08-30
                          M................
                       ...                ....
                     ...                      ..
                    ..         ...........      .
                  ..        ...   ....   ...     ..
                  .       ..  ....   .....  ..    .
                 .       ..  ..          ... ..    .
                 .      ..  .   ........   .  ..   .
                 .      .  .   ..      ..   .  .   .
                 .      .  ..  .    S  ..   .  .   .
                 .      ..  .  ..     ..   .V ..   .
                 ..      .. ... ..m....  ...  E   .
                  ..      ..  ....    ....  ..   ..
                   ..      ....   .....   ...   ..
                     ..       ............    ..
                       ..                   ..
                         ....          .....
                             ..........


Installation
------------

asciiplanets is a Python 3 script and requires the following Python
libraries:

    - pyephem

Whether you install those libraries using PIP or via your distribution's
package manager is up to you.

If you're using Arch Linux, you can use the following AUR package:

    - https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/asciiplanets-git/


Running
-------

You run the program on a VT220-ish text terminal:

    $ asciiplanets

Refer to the manpage for all options.
